Boil a large #pot{} of salted water with @water{to taste} for the rice.

Add the @basmati rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}. Drain in a #sieve{}
and pop back in the pot.

Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1%unit}. Halve
lengthways, then thinly slice.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Cut the @Irish chicken breast{320%grams} into 2cm pieces.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{to taste} in a large pan over medium-high heat.

Add the diced chicken and brown on all sides for ~{3-4%mins} (it should not be
fully cooked yet).

Add @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Transfer chicken out of the pan.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat and melt a knob of @butter{to
taste}.

Add the leeks, salt and pepper. Reduce heat to medium, cover and cook
~{8-10%mins}, or until tender.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%unit} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @parsley{10%grams} (stalks and all).

Once the leeks are cooked and tender, remove the lid.

Add the chicken, garlic, @cream{250%grams} and half the @grated Italian style
hard cheese{25%grams}. Mix and let reduce for ~{5-7%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve the rice on plates and spoon the chicken and leek sauce on top.

Sprinkle with chopped parsley and remaining grated cheese.